  "body": "### User Story\n\nAs a user I want to have a clear and non-confusing UI to send/receive ether or tokens or use dapps.\n\n### Description\n\n*Type*: Design\n\n*Context*:  \n\nWord \"transaction\" refers to two different concepts. \nThe first is like a bank transaction - an operation where some money goes from A to B.\nThe second one is a bit more general - a set of operations that changes some state atomically.\n\nRight now we want to focus on the simpler transfer use cases:\n- A sends 1 eth to B (and pays for the tx costs)\n- A sends 45 HND to B, etc. (and pays for the tx costs)\n\nHowever, more complex cases are possible:\n- A sends 0.02 eth to a smart contract and receives 10 HND back\n- A sends 0.03 eth and 20 HND to a smart contract and receives 30 LXS back, B receives a cut of 2 HND, etc.\n\nThe simpler use cases will typically be seen in direct interaction between users and the complex ones as result of some kind of dapp usage.\n\nThe one thing common to all those transactions, simple or complex alike, is that they cost gas. So, they all actually affect A's ether balance if nothing else.\n\n*Summary*:\n\nFind a way to:\n- Display simple and complex transactions in a different way\n- Possibly to separate them\n- Display transactions where multiple transfers of value occur",
